<subSubSection id="C31CCA91FFE6174CA1DFF9C45EB8FAB4" pageId="11" pageNumber="210" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BB9991AFFE6174CA1DFF9C4596AFCA3" blockId="11.[163,779,1630,1898]" lastBlockId="11.[827,1443,197,894]" pageId="11" pageNumber="210">
<emphasis id="B9724508FFE6174CA1DFF9C45C53F9AA" box="[163,294,1631,1652]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="210">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
Among the 
<taxonomicName id="4C06E299FFE6174CA0B5F9C55F39F9AA" authorityName="Lepeletier de Saint Fargeau" authorityYear="1841" box="[457,588,1630,1652]" pageId="11" pageNumber="199" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Colletinae">Colletinae</taxonomicName>
, the species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C06E299FFE6174CA1DFF9E65D8EF94C" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" box="[163,251,1661,1682]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="210" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9724508FFE6174CA1DFF9E65D8EF94C" box="[163,251,1661,1682]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="210">Colletes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be readily diagnosed by the subhorizontal surface of the metapostnotum with a series of longitudinal carinae or sinuous short striae (modified from: 
<bibRefCitation id="EF97E4EBFFE6174CA194F9425CEFF930" author="Michener CD" box="[232,410,1753,1775]" pageId="11" pageNumber="210" pagination="22 - 703" refId="ref12360" refString="Michener CD. 1989. Classification of American Colletinae (Hymenoptera, Apoidea). University of Kansas Science Bulletin 53: 22 - 703." type="journal article" year="1989">Michener, 1989</bibRefCitation>
; see also 
<figureCitation id="133D859FFFE6174CA370F9425F15F930" box="[524,608,1753,1775]" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="4.[146,225,1432,1454]" captionTargetBox="[305,1265,195,1390]" captionTargetId="figure-197@4.[305,1265,195,1392]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figure 4. Diagnostic features of Colletinae. Numbers shown in red indicate derived character states. A, B, Lateral view of male propodeum, Trichocolletes dowerinensis (A) and Colletes gilvus (B); C–E, posterior view of male metapostnotum, Xanthocotelles atacama (C), Hemicotelles magallanes (D) and C. atripes (E); F, ventral view of male S7 of Mourecotelles sp.1. Scale bars = 1 mm." pageId="11" pageNumber="210">Fig. 4E</figureCitation>
) in both sexes [subhorizontal surface of the metapostnotum without carinae or striae (
<figureCitation id="133D859FFFE6174CA011F88D5CA8F8F2" box="[365,477,1814,1836]" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="4.[146,225,1432,1454]" captionTargetBox="[305,1265,195,1390]" captionTargetId="figure-197@4.[305,1265,195,1392]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figure 4. Diagnostic features of Colletinae. Numbers shown in red indicate derived character states. A, B, Lateral view of male propodeum, Trichocolletes dowerinensis (A) and Colletes gilvus (B); C–E, posterior view of male metapostnotum, Xanthocotelles atacama (C), Hemicotelles magallanes (D) and C. atripes (E); F, ventral view of male S7 of Mourecotelles sp.1. Scale bars = 1 mm." pageId="11" pageNumber="210">Fig. 4C, D</figureCitation>
) in both sexes of the other genera]. Also, the second recurrent vein of the forewing is almost always sigmoidal in 
<taxonomicName id="4C06E299FFE6174CA080F8CF5F20F8B7" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" box="[508,597,1876,1897]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="210" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9724508FFE6174CA080F8CF5F20F8B7" box="[508,597,1876,1897]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="210">Colletes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(modified from: 
<bibRefCitation id="EF97E4EBFFE6174CA247FF5D594EFF04" author="Toro H &amp; Cabezas V" box="[827,1083,197,219]" pageId="11" pageNumber="210" pagination="45 - 64" refId="ref13000" refString="Toro H, Cabezas V. 1977. Nuevos generos y especies de Colletini sudamericanos, segunda parte. Anales del Museo de Historia Natural de Valpariso 10: 45 - 64." type="journal article" year="1977">Toro &amp; Cabezas, 1977</bibRefCitation>
; see also 
<figureCitation id="133D859FFFE6174CA5D2FF5E5876FF04" box="[1198,1283,197,219]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="3.[163,242,1397,1419]" captionTargetBox="[323,1283,195,1357]" captionTargetId="figure-203@3.[323,1283,195,1357]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figure 3. Diagnostic features of Colletinae. Numbers shown in red indicate derived character states. A–D, lateral view of male forewing, Hexantheda entrerriana (A), Hemicotelles ruizii (B), C. albomaculatus (C) and C. rufipes (D); E, F, dorsal view of female metasomal apex, C. gilvus (E) and Bicolletes rufiventris (F). Scale bars = 1 mm." pageId="11" pageNumber="210">Fig. 3D</figureCitation>
), although in a few species of the genus (e.g. 
<taxonomicName id="4C06E299FFE6174CA5DEFF7F58D7FF24" authority="Smith, 1854" authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1854" box="[1186,1442,228,250]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="210" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atripes">
<emphasis id="B9724508FFE6174CA5DEFF7F5865FF27" box="[1186,1296,228,249]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="210">C. atripes</emphasis>
Smith, 1854
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C06E299FFE6174CA20DFE985963FEC9" authorityName="Moure" authorityYear="1943" box="[881,1046,258,280]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Rhynchocolletes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="210" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albicinctus">
<emphasis id="B9724508FFE6174CA20DFE985963FEC9" box="[881,1046,258,280]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="210">C. albicinctus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) it may be only slightly arcuate outwardly (
<figureCitation id="133D859FFFE6174CA2B5FEBA5957FEE8" box="[969,1058,289,311]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="3.[163,242,1397,1419]" captionTargetBox="[323,1283,195,1357]" captionTargetId="figure-203@3.[323,1283,195,1357]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figure 3. Diagnostic features of Colletinae. Numbers shown in red indicate derived character states. A–D, lateral view of male forewing, Hexantheda entrerriana (A), Hemicotelles ruizii (B), C. albomaculatus (C) and C. rufipes (D); E, F, dorsal view of female metasomal apex, C. gilvus (E) and Bicolletes rufiventris (F). Scale bars = 1 mm." pageId="11" pageNumber="210">Fig. 3C</figureCitation>
), as it is in both 
<taxonomicName id="4C06E299FFE6174CA581FEBA58D7FEE8" authorityName="Toro &amp; Cabezas" authorityYear="1977" box="[1277,1442,289,310]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Mourecotelles" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="210" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9724508FFE6174CA581FEBA58D7FEE8" box="[1277,1442,289,310]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="210">Mourecotelles</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C06E299FFE6174CA20EFEDB5957FE8B" authorityName="Toro &amp; Cabezas" authorityYear="1978" box="[882,1058,320,341]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Xanthocotelles" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="210" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9724508FFE6174CA20EFEDB5957FE8B" box="[882,1058,320,341]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="210">Xanthocotelles</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C06E299FFE6174CA54FFEDB59E7FE8B" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" box="[1075,1170,320,341]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="210" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9724508FFE6174CA54FFEDB59E7FE8B" box="[1075,1170,320,341]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="210">Colletes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is also unique among the 
<taxonomicName id="4C06E299FFE6174CA214FEC55EAAFEAA" authorityName="Lepeletier de Saint Fargeau" authorityYear="1841" box="[872,991,350,372]" pageId="11" pageNumber="199" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Colletinae">Colletinae</taxonomicName>
in having the horizontal surface of T1 subequal in length to T 
<quantity id="4CFE34FFFFE6174CA521FEE659F8FE4D" box="[1117,1165,381,403]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.08" pageId="11" pageNumber="210" unit="in" value="2.0">2 in</quantity>
males (modified from: 
<bibRefCitation id="EF97E4EBFFE6174CA247FE075E9CFE6F" author="Michener CD" box="[827,1001,412,434]" pageId="11" pageNumber="210" pagination="22 - 703" refId="ref12360" refString="Michener CD. 1989. Classification of American Colletinae (Hymenoptera, Apoidea). University of Kansas Science Bulletin 53: 22 - 703." type="journal article" year="1989">Michener, 1989</bibRefCitation>
; see also Supporting Information, Fig. S12D) [horizontal surface of T1 much shorter than T2 (Supporting Information, Fig. S12C) in males of 
<taxonomicName id="4C06E299FFE6174CA247FE635EBFFDD3" authorityName="Toro &amp; Cabezas" authorityYear="1977" box="[827,970,504,525]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Hemicotelles" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="210" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9724508FFE6174CA247FE635EBFFDD3" box="[827,970,504,525]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="210">Hemicotelles</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C06E299FFE6174CA2AAFE635905FDD3" authorityName="Toro &amp; Cabezas" authorityYear="1977" box="[982,1136,504,525]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Mourecotelles" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="210" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9724508FFE6174CA2AAFE635905FDD3" box="[982,1136,504,525]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="210">Mourecotelles</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C06E299FFE6174CA5D5FE635838FDD3" authorityName="Toro &amp; Cabezas" authorityYear="1978" box="[1193,1357,504,525]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Xanthocotelles" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="210" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9724508FFE6174CA5D5FE635838FDD3" box="[1193,1357,504,525]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="210">Xanthocotelles</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, except 
<taxonomicName id="4C06E299FFE6174CA247FD8C5EA8FDF5" authorityName="Toro &amp; Cabezas" authorityYear="1978" box="[827,989,534,556]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Xanthocotelles" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="210" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="basitarsalis">
<emphasis id="B9724508FFE6174CA247FD8C5EA8FDF5" box="[827,989,534,556]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="210">X. basitarsalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C06E299FFE6174CA569FD8C59FDFDF5" authorityName="Toro &amp; Cabezas" authorityYear="1978" box="[1045,1160,534,556]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Xanthocotelles" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="210" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tarsalis">
<emphasis id="B9724508FFE6174CA569FD8C59FDFDF5" box="[1045,1160,534,556]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="210">X. tarsalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
]. Females of 
<taxonomicName id="4C06E299FFE6174CA461FD8D5800FDF5" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" box="[1309,1397,534,555]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="210" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9724508FFE6174CA461FD8D5800FDF5" box="[1309,1397,534,555]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="210">Colletes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be further differentiated from those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C06E299FFE6174CA58EFDAE58F4FD94" authorityName="Toro &amp; Cabezas" authorityYear="1977" box="[1266,1409,565,586]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Hemicotelles" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="210" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9724508FFE6174CA58EFDAE58F4FD94" box="[1266,1409,565,586]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="210">Hemicotelles</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by T6 without a posteromedial longitudinal ridge (this study; Supporting Information, Figs S9A–C) [T6 with such a ridge (Supporting Information, Fig. S11B) in 
<taxonomicName id="4C06E299FFE6174CA247FD2B5EA5FD1B" authorityName="Toro &amp; Cabezas" authorityYear="1977" box="[827,976,688,709]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Hemicotelles" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="210" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9724508FFE6174CA247FD2B5EA5FD1B" box="[827,976,688,709]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="210">Hemicotelles</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
]; and from those of both 
<taxonomicName id="4C06E299FFE6174CA47EFD2B58D6FD1B" authorityName="Toro &amp; Cabezas" authorityYear="1977" box="[1282,1443,688,709]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Mourecotelles" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="210" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9724508FFE6174CA47EFD2B58D6FD1B" box="[1282,1443,688,709]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="210">Mourecotelles</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C06E299FFE6174CA217FD55597AFD3D" authorityName="Toro &amp; Cabezas" authorityYear="1978" box="[875,1039,718,739]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Xanthocotelles" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="210" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9724508FFE6174CA217FD55597AFD3D" box="[875,1039,718,739]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="210">Xanthocotelles</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by apical and preapical mandibular teeth forming an obtuse angle (modified from: 
<bibRefCitation id="EF97E4EBFFE6174CA412FD765971FCFF" author="Toro H &amp; Cabezas V" pageId="11" pageNumber="210" pagination="45 - 64" refId="ref13000" refString="Toro H, Cabezas V. 1977. Nuevos generos y especies de Colletini sudamericanos, segunda parte. Anales del Museo de Historia Natural de Valpariso 10: 45 - 64." type="journal article" year="1977">Toro &amp; Cabezas, 1977</bibRefCitation>
; see also Supporting Information, 
<figureCitation id="133D859FFFE6174CA247FCB15ED7FC9E" box="[827,930,810,832]" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="8.[146,226,938,960]" captionTargetBox="[146,1422,197,896]" captionTargetId="figure-470@8.[145,1425,195,898]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figure 6. Most-parsimonious tree (part two) from the EW analysis showing character state changes. Black rectangles represent unique changes and white rectangles represent homoplastic ones. Character numbers are indicated above branches and the corresponding state changes below the branches. Asterisks indicate type species of the genus. The position of Colletes clypeonitens is doubtful (see text). The Colletinae shown are (from top to bottom) Hemicotelles ruizii, C. cyanescens, C. nigritulus and C. slevini." pageId="11" pageNumber="210">Fig. S6E</figureCitation>
) [mandibular teeth forming a right angle (Supporting Information, 
<figureCitation id="133D859FFFE6174CA512FCD259A7FC81" box="[1134,1234,841,863]" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="8.[146,226,938,960]" captionTargetBox="[146,1422,197,896]" captionTargetId="figure-470@8.[145,1425,195,898]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figure 6. Most-parsimonious tree (part two) from the EW analysis showing character state changes. Black rectangles represent unique changes and white rectangles represent homoplastic ones. Character numbers are indicated above branches and the corresponding state changes below the branches. Asterisks indicate type species of the genus. The position of Colletes clypeonitens is doubtful (see text). The Colletinae shown are (from top to bottom) Hemicotelles ruizii, C. cyanescens, C. nigritulus and C. slevini." pageId="11" pageNumber="210">Fig. S6F</figureCitation>
) in 
<taxonomicName id="4C06E299FFE6174CA47FFCD258D6FC80" authorityName="Toro &amp; Cabezas" authorityYear="1977" box="[1283,1443,841,862]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Mourecotelles" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="210" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9724508FFE6174CA47FFCD258D6FC80" box="[1283,1443,841,862]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="210">Mourecotelles</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C06E299FFE6174CA210FCF35965FCA3" authorityName="Toro &amp; Cabezas" authorityYear="1978" box="[876,1040,872,893]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Xanthocotelles" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="210" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9724508FFE6174CA210FCF35965FCA3" box="[876,1040,872,893]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="210">Xanthocotelles</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
].
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB9991AFFE6174CA247FC3D5918FC04" blockId="11.[827,1442,934,987]" pageId="11" pageNumber="210">
<emphasis id="B9724508FFE6174CA247FC3D5960FC62" box="[827,1045,934,956]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="210">Additional species:</emphasis>
For an updated checklist refer to 
<bibRefCitation id="EF97E4EBFFE6174CA247FC5E5913FC05" author="Ascher JS &amp; Pickering J" box="[827,1126,965,987]" pageId="11" pageNumber="210" refId="ref11055" refString="Ascher JS, Pickering J. 2020. Discover Life bee species guide and world checklist (Hymenoptera: Apoidea: Anthophila). Available at: http: // www. discoverlife. org / mp / 20 q? guide = Apoidea _ species (accessed 5 March 2020)." type="url" year="2020">Ascher &amp; Pickering (2020)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB9991AFFE6174CA247FB9F5EB8FAB4" blockId="11.[827,1443,1028,1386]" pageId="11" pageNumber="210">
<emphasis id="B9724508FFE6174CA247FB9F5952FBC7" box="[827,1063,1028,1049]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="210">
Comments: 
<taxonomicName id="4C06E299FFE6174CA2B7FB9F5952FBC7" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" box="[971,1063,1028,1049]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="210" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Colletes</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
includes representatives on all continents inhabited by bees (except Oceania), and is by far the most diverse genus of 
<taxonomicName id="4C06E299FFE6174CA5DAFBDA586EFB89" authorityName="Lepeletier de Saint Fargeau" authorityYear="1841" box="[1190,1307,1089,1111]" pageId="11" pageNumber="199" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Colletinae">Colletinae</taxonomicName>
with nearly 520 valid described species (
<bibRefCitation id="EF97E4EBFFE6174CA504FBFB58E0FBAB" author="Ascher JS &amp; Pickering J" box="[1144,1429,1120,1142]" pageId="11" pageNumber="210" refId="ref11055" refString="Ascher JS, Pickering J. 2020. Discover Life bee species guide and world checklist (Hymenoptera: Apoidea: Anthophila). Available at: http: // www. discoverlife. org / mp / 20 q? guide = Apoidea _ species (accessed 5 March 2020)." type="url" year="2020">Ascher &amp; Pickering, 2020</bibRefCitation>
), from a suggested total estimated to be 700 (
<bibRefCitation id="EF97E4EBFFE6174CA454FBE55ECFFB6C" author="Kuhlmann M &amp; Almeida EAB &amp; Laurenne N &amp; Quicke DLJ" pageId="11" pageNumber="210" pagination="291 - 318" refId="ref12134" refString="Kuhlmann M, Almeida EAB, Laurenne N, Quicke DLJ. 2009. Molecular phylogeny and biogeography of the bee genus Colletes Latreille, 1802 (Hymenoptera: Apiformis: Colletidae), based on mitochondrial COI and nuclear 28 S nuclear sequence data. Insect Systematics &amp; Evolution 40: 291 - 318." type="journal article" year="2009">
Kuhlmann 
<emphasis id="B9724508FFE6174CA247FB055E01FB6C" box="[827,884,1181,1203]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="210">et al.</emphasis>
, 2009
</bibRefCitation>
). Indeed, the large number of new species described in recent taxonomic treatments of the genus [reviewed by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF97E4EBFFE6174CA2ABFB4159C8FB2E" author="Ferrari RR &amp; Onuferko TM &amp; Monckton SK &amp; Packer L" box="[983,1213,1242,1264]" pageId="11" pageNumber="210" pagination="106750" refId="ref11654" refString="Ferrari RR, Onuferko TM, Monckton SK, Packer L. 2020. The evolutionary history of the cellophane bee genus Colletes Latreille (Hymenoptera: Colletidae): molecular phylogeny, biogeography and implications for a global infrageneric classification. Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution 146: 106750." type="journal article" year="2020">
Ferrari 
<emphasis id="B9724508FFE6174CA54EFB405919FB31" box="[1074,1132,1242,1264]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="210">et al.</emphasis>
(2020)
</bibRefCitation>
] suggest that there is still a considerable number of species yet to be discovered. As delimited herein, 
<taxonomicName id="4C06E299FFE6174CA5D3FA83587DFAF3" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" box="[1199,1288,1304,1325]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="210" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9724508FFE6174CA5D3FA83587DFAF3" box="[1199,1288,1304,1325]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="210">Colletes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also includes 
<taxonomicName id="4C06E299FFE6174CA247FAAD5E86FA95" authorityName="Moure" authorityYear="1943" box="[827,1011,1334,1355]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Rhynchocolletes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="210" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9724508FFE6174CA247FAAD5E86FA95" box="[827,1011,1334,1355]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="210">Rhynchocolletes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as previously proposed by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF97E4EBFFE6174CA449FAAD5E0CFAB4" author="Michener CD" pageId="11" pageNumber="210" pagination="22 - 703" refId="ref12360" refString="Michener CD. 1989. Classification of American Colletinae (Hymenoptera, Apoidea). University of Kansas Science Bulletin 53: 22 - 703." type="journal article" year="1989">Michener (1989</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EF97E4EBFFE6174CA2FBFACE5ECBFAB4" author="Michener CD" box="[903,958,1365,1386]" pageId="11" pageNumber="210" refId="ref12386" refString="Michener CD. 2007. The bees of the world, 2 nd edn. Baltimore: Johns Hopkins University Press." type="book" year="2007">2007</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
